The big boys were all kept apart in the draw for the quarter final of the FA Cup on Thursday. The draw took place ahead of Everton's last-16 tie against Boreham Wood, with England boss Gareth Southgate picking out the numbers. Crystal Palace were the first name out of the hat, and they will face the Toffees after they beat Wood 2-0. Championship sides Nottingham Forest and Huddersfield take each other on next Monday, and the winners will host Liverpool. Middlesbrough, who have already stunned Manchester United and Tottenham, were next out, and they will play Chelsea at the Riverside. And finally, Southampton will take on the Premier League champions Manchester City at St Mary's. Here is a look back at how the draw unfolded...